<POST>
<POSTER> Terry S &lt;tschw10...@aol.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-10-20T23:25:00 </POSTDATE>
Bought a very cheap (1 cent!) item on ebay today. The auction stated:
Shipping costs: Check item description and payment instructions or
contact seller for details.

Nothing in the description regarding shipping.

Got the invoice, $16 &quot;flat rate&quot; shipping!!!

I know, my fault for not emailing the seller I guess. FYI, this item
is an old Mallory UHF converter that I wanted only for the case. Will
become a nixie tube clock.

For the record, I had bid 9 cents.

I was prepared for $7 to maybe $9 shipping... but $16??? I did gripe a
bit as I made the payment. No response yet.

Maybe I'm just torqued because the shipping is 1600 times the closing
price... but I don't think I'm out of line. I've never charged a penny
over the actual shipping costs for an item I've sold... every bit of
packaging recycled/reused. No charge for my time, handling, tape,
nuthin'. All gratis.

In my opinion, &quot;flat rate&quot; shipping is just another way for sellers to
line their pockets with unjustified charges.

At the very least, ebay ought to require that &quot;flat rate&quot; charges be
disclosed up front.

Your thoughts?

Terry
