It's called the eBay User Agreement.  When you join eBay, you are obligated to follow
it's rules.  Each time you bid, you are told that a high bid is a binding contract,
that you must follow through with.  You are warned repeatedly on the site to check
the shipping with the seller if it isn't listed in the description before bidding, as
your bid, if high, will be entering you into a binding contract.

It's this simple:  Follow the rules you've agreed to by joining eBay and placing
bids.  Why is that so hard to understand?
